  "text": "The Kafka producer's TimeoutException for expiring record batches is triggered through the following chain:\n\n1. **TimeoutException Definition** (apache/kafka:clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/errors/TimeoutException.java): The `TimeoutException` class extends `RetriableException` and is thrown when a request times out or batches expire.\n\n2. **Record Batch Expiration Logic**: The expiration is checked in multiple places:\n   - `RecordAccumulator.expiredBatches(long now)` (apache/kafka:clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java, line 465): Iterates through all accumulated batches and checks if they have reached the delivery timeout by calling `batch.hasReachedDeliveryTimeout(deliveryTimeoutMs, now)`.\n   - `Sender.getExpiredInflightBatches(long now)` (apache/kafka:clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java, line 180): Checks in-flight batches that have reached delivery timeout using the same `hasReachedDeliveryTimeout` check.\n   - Both methods are invoked from `Sender.sendProducerData(long now)` (apache/kafka:clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java, line 357), which collects expired batches and fails them with a `TimeoutException`.\n\n3. **Timeout Check** (apache/kafka:clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/ProducerBatch.java, line 438): The `ProducerBatch.hasReachedDeliveryTimeout(long deliveryTimeoutMs, long now)` method returns true when the elapsed time since batch creation exceeds `deliveryTimeoutMs`.\n\n4. **Configuration Constant** (apache/kafka:clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/ProducerConfig.java, line 165): The `DELIVERY_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG` constant defines \"delivery.timeout.ms\", which is an upper bound on the time to report success or failure after a send() call returns. The default value is 120 seconds (120 * 1000 ms). When a batch's creation time exceeds this timeout, `Sender.sendProducerData()` calls `failBatch()` with a `TimeoutException` containing the error message \"Expiring N record(s) for topic-partition\"."
}

